What DVWA is and why it exists

DVWA (Damn Vulnerable Web Application) is an intentionally insecure web application designed only for learning and training.

Purpose of DVWA

DVWA is built to:

Teach how vulnerabilities actually appear in code

Let learners safely exploit common web flaws

Connect theory (OWASP Top 10) with hands-on exploitation

Show how developer mistakes lead to real security issues

âš ï¸ DVWA is not malware, and itâ€™s not for attacking real systems.
It exists so you can legally and ethically learn exploitation.

